<DOC><DOCNO> AP890204-0050 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-04-89 0521EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Cat'sHouse     02-04 0149</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Cat's House,0151</SECOND><HEAD>Cat For Sale For $236,000, With House Tossed In</HEAD><DATELINE>MARKET DRAYTON, England (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Figaro the cat is on the marketfor $236,250 _ the only catch is that the house goes with him.   Peter Glanfield, a business consultant, said the black-and-whitePersian feline ``adopted'' his four-bedroom home in this centralEngland town several years ago, and he called it unfair to separateFigaro from it.   So the cat's picture was printed on the front of home's realestate flier, and prospective buyers were warned they cannot buy thehouse without Figaro.   ``The elegant feline comes complete with a freehold Victorianresidence of character in order to keep him in the style to which heis accustomed,'' said the flier, which described Figaro as a ``largefriendly cat.''   ``It really is a case of no puss, no purchase,'' real estateagent Richard Taylor said Friday.</TEXT></DOC>